Do not modify files unless the user explicitly asks for fixes.

## C# / .NET

When a `.csproj` or solution exists:

- Run `dotnet build`; run `dotnet test` if test projects exist.
- Use repo-standard formatters or analyzers if that is how the project gates quality.

Report with paths or snippets when useful: logic bugs; null/async/disposal mistakes; WPF UI-thread issues; concurrency races affecting correctness or UX; hardcoded secrets.

## Security

Tailor depth to the app: desktop WPF vs services or networked code. Consider injection, unsafe deserialization, and auth/session flaws where relevant.

## Cursor workspace (read-only)

- **Rules**: frontmatter valid; scope clear; no contradictions with sibling rules.
- **Skills**: `name` + `description` present; triggers in description; body actionable; links resolve if present.
- **Agents**: role clear; honor `readonly` where set; no stale cross-references.

Check for broken markdown fences and contradictory guidance across rules, skills, and agents for the same workflow.

```text
[Critical|High|Medium] <risk>: <path/lines or snippet> — <reason>
```
